# Scaffold Feature

Create a new feature end-to-end across all platforms.

## Instructions

1. Ask for feature name and description if not provided.

2. Run advisory board review (read `docs/advisory-board.md`, evaluate from each perspective).

3. Create feature doc: `docs/features/{name}.md` (use `docs/features/_template.md`).

4. Create/update entity docs in `docs/entities/`.

5. Add endpoints to `shared/api-contracts/openapi.yml` (follow `docs/api/conventions.md`).

6. Run `task generate-clients`.

{% if "backend" in platforms %}7. Implement backend: controller, service, repository, entity, DTOs, migration in `backend/`.{% endif %}

{% if "web" in platforms %}8. Implement web client pages in `web/`.{% endif %}

{% if "admin" in platforms %}9. Implement admin portal pages in `admin/`.{% endif %}

{% if "android" in platforms %}10. Implement Android: Screen + ViewModel (MVVM) in `android/`.{% endif %}

{% if "ios" in platforms %}11. Implement iOS: View + ViewModel (MVVM) in `ios/`.{% endif %}

12. Update feature doc implementation status.

## Key Patterns

- API-first: OpenAPI spec is source of truth
- MVVM on both Android and iOS
- One ViewModel per screen
- Repository pattern (interface/protocol + implementation)
- Documentation before code
